body:
# Assistants Threads

Threads are persistent conversation containers in the Assistants API. They hold messages, manage context automatically, and serve as the execution target for assistant runs.

## Thread Lifecycle

```
Create Thread -> Add Messages -> Create Run -> Poll/Stream -> Read Response -> (repeat)
```

## Create and Use a Thread

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

// Create a thread
const thread = await client.beta.threads.create();
console.log(`Thread ID: ${thread.id}`);

// Add a user message
await client.beta.threads.messages.create(thread.id, {
  role: "user",
  content: "Analyze the performance implications of using async/await vs callbacks in Node.js.",
});

// Run the assistant
const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.createAndPoll(thread.id, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
});

if (run.status === "completed") {
  const messages = await client.beta.threads.messages.list(thread.id);
  const response = messages.data[0].content[0].text.value;
  console.log(response);
}
```

## Create Thread with Initial Messages

```javascript
const thread = await client.beta.threads.create({
  messages: [
    { role: "user", content: "I need help with database optimization." },
  ],
});
```

## Message Operations

```javascript
// Add a message
const message = await client.beta.threads.messages.create(thread.id, {
  role: "user",
  content: "What about indexing strategies?",
});

// List messages (most recent first)
const messages = await client.beta.threads.messages.list(thread.id, {
  order: "desc",
  limit: 20,
});

// Retrieve a specific message
const msg = await client.beta.threads.messages.retrieve(thread.id, message.id);
```

## Message with File Attachments

```javascript
await client.beta.threads.messages.create(thread.id, {
  role: "user",
  content: "Analyze this CSV data.",
  attachments: [
    {
      file_id: "file-abc123",
      tools: [{ type: "code_interpreter" }],
    },
  ],
});
```

## Thread Management

```javascript
// Retrieve thread metadata
const thread = await client.beta.threads.retrieve(threadId);

// Update thread metadata
await client.beta.threads.update(threadId, {
  metadata: { session: "user-session-42", topic: "database-optimization" },
});

// Delete thread (permanently removes all messages)
await client.beta.threads.del(threadId);
```

## Context Window Management

The API automatically manages context windows. When a thread's messages exceed the model's context limit, the API truncates older messages. You can control this with the `truncation_strategy` on runs:

```javascript
const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.create(thread.id, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
  truncation_strategy: {
    type: "last_messages",
    last_messages: 10,  // only use the last 10 messages
  },
});
```

scripts.inline:
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

const assistantId = process.env.ASSISTANT_ID;
if (!assistantId) throw new Error("ASSISTANT_ID is required");

const userMessage = process.env.USER_MESSAGE || "Hello!";
const threadId = process.env.THREAD_ID;

// Create or reuse thread
const thread = threadId
  ? await client.beta.threads.retrieve(threadId)
  : await client.beta.threads.create();

console.error(`Thread: ${thread.id}`);

// Add user message
await client.beta.threads.messages.create(thread.id, {
  role: "user",
  content: userMessage,
});

// Run assistant and poll to completion
const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.createAndPoll(thread.id, {
  assistant_id: assistantId,
});

if (run.status === "completed") {
  const messages = await client.beta.threads.messages.list(thread.id, { order: "desc", limit: 1 });
  const response = messages.data[0].content[0].text.value;
  console.log(JSON.stringify({ threadId: thread.id, runId: run.id, response }, null, 2));
} else {
  console.error(`Run ended with status: ${run.status}`);
  if (run.last_error) console.error(run.last_error);
  process.exit(1);
}
